	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-01-13T00:13:54">The Parkmead Group plc is engaged in the oil and gas exploration and production and the provision of energy sector economics, valuations and benchmarking. The Company operates in two segments: oil and gas exploration and production segment and energy economics segment. The oil and gas exploration and production segment invests in oil and gas exploration and production assets. Parkmead produces approximately 2,300 barrels of oil equivalent per day from five oil and gas fields across the United Kingdom and the Netherlands. The Companys development projects include the Greater Perth area, the Platypus gas development in the Southern North Sea and development projects in the Netherlands. Parkmead has interests in exploration blocks in the United Kingdom and Netherlands. The energy economics segment provides energy sector economics, valuation and benchmarking, advising on energy policies and fiscal matters, undertaking economic evaluations, supplying benchmarking services and training.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2015-12-10T20:55:40">BRIEF: For the fiscal year ended 30 June 2015, The Parkmead Group plc revenues decreased 24% to L18.6M. Net loss totaled L31.4M vs. income of L1.2M. Revenues reflect Oil and Gas Exploration segment decrease of 25% to L17.7M, Benchmarking Services segment decrease of 21% to L967K, Europe segment decrease of 25% to L18.1M, USA segment decrease of 35% to L306K.</Text>
	</TextInfo>
